<appendix id="app.deployment.docupdates">
 <title>Documentation Updates</title>
 <para>
  This chapter lists content changes for this document since the release of
  &productnamereg; 11 SP3.
 </para>
 <para>
  This manual was updated on the following dates:
 </para>
<!--list of xrefs, latest date sorted upmost-->
 <itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    <xref linkend="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga_maint1" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
   </para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    <xref linkend="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
   </para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
 
 <sect1 id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga_maint1">
  <title>January 2015 (Documentation Maintenance Update)</title>
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>Password Settings, Expiration Date is expiring user accounts in
        YAST Users module (<ulink
         url="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=743874"></ulink>).</para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
 
 <sect1 id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga">
  <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>

  <variablelist>
<!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
   <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
	       href="common_docupdates_general_i.xml"/>
<!-- 2. Installation on AMD64 and Intel 64 -->
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.x86"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated system requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 3. Installation on IBM POWER  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.power"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added POWER8 to the list of supported hardware (Fate#315272).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sls; 12 for POWER has moved to Little Endian. Updated affected
        parts of the documentation.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 4. Installation on IBM System z -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.zseries"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the list of supported platforms: Removed IBM Series z9 and
        z10 machines and added IBM zEnterprise BC12.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the memory and disk space requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed instructions on how to IPL from tape&mdash;this is no longer
        supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Rewrote large parts of <xref linkend="sec.prep.netcfg"/> to remove
        redundant information and make it more concise.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed references to Token Ring, which is no longer supported
        (Fate#313154).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 6. Installation with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.inst"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote the chapter because of the new installation
        workflow.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation routine now supports setting up multiple network
        devices during the installation (Fate#315680):
        <xref
	linkend="sec.i.yast2.network"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation proposal contains a separate
        <filename>/home</filename> partition formatted with XFS (Fate#316637
        and Fate#316624):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.partitioning"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed occurrences of the &yast; Repair module which has been
        dropped (Fate#308670).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Update repositories are added after having registered with &scc; and
        can be used during installation (Fate#312012):
        <xref
	linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Extensions and modules can be added to the system during the
        installation (Fate#316548):
        <xref
	linkend="sec.i.yast2.conf.manual.cc"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sled; can be installed as an add-on on top of &sls; (Fate#316436):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        The HW crypto stack for IBM &zseries; can be selected for
        installation via a pattern (Fate#316143):
        <xref
       linkend="sec.i.yast2.proposal.sofware"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Automatically importing SSH keys from a previous installation can be
        disabled (Fate#314982):
        <xref
	linkend="sec.i.yast.start.parameters.keys_users"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 7. Updating SUSE Linux Enterprise -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added new section: <xref linkend="sec.update.sle12"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 8. Setting Up Hardware Components with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.y2.hw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed the following sections as the respective &yast; modules are
        no longer included: <citetitle>Hardware Information</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Setting Up Graphics Card and Monitor</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Mouse Model</citetitle>, and <citetitle>Setting Up a
        Scanner</citetitle>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed content about mouse setup and adjusted
        <xref
       linkend="cha.y2.hw.keym"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 9. Installing or Removing Software -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.y2.sw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> because of changes
        in the GNOME software updater.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 10. Installing Add-On Products  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.add-ons"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Installing add-on products or software extensions is now also
        possible without access to physical media. Added the following new
        sections: <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.register"/> and
        <xref
	linkend="sec.add-ons.extensions"/>. Modified
        <xref
	linkend="sec.add-ons.install"/> accordingly.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 16. Subscription Management -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.smt"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        For registering clients against an &smt; server,
        <command>suse_register</command> has been replaced with
        <command>SUSEConnect</command> (Fate#316585).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated chapter <xref linkend="cha.addon_creator"/> according to
        <ulink
     url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=861855"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated chapter <xref linkend="cha.productcreator"/> and added
        chapter <xref linkend="cha.imgcreator"/> according to
        <ulink
     url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=864033"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated section <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> according to
        <ulink
	url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=839692"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed section <citetitle>Using Fingerprint
        Authentication</citetitle>. Further minor corrections and additions
        (<ulink url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857680"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed obsolete parameter <literal>OsaMedium</literal> from
        parmfile and Cobbler examples
        (<ulink
	url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=860404"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Additions in section <xref linkend="sec.fb.customize"/>
        (<ulink
	url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=861866"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added instructions on how to add secondary languages during
        installation
        (<ulink
	url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=870482"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--Installing Multiple Kernel Versions -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.tuning.multikernel"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Multiversion feature (more than one kernel installed) is enabled by
        default
        (<ulink
        url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Warn about incompatible Kernel Module Packages (KPMs)
        (<ulink
        url="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
</appendix>
